Can Track provides real-time transaction monitoring and push notifications via Telegram for Canton Network accounts. Users add their accounts and receive instant, formatted alerts for transfers, validator rewards, and app rewards directly on their mobile devices or laptops. This eliminates the need to constantly check the Canton explorer and provides immediate awareness of account activity. Potential future expansion to a web application component.

According to CIP-0067, this voting proposal is a One-Time Allocation of Historical Unclaimed Rewards to the Global Synchronizer Foundation (GSF). The vote covers the transfer of the entire balance of unclaimed rewards from the pool to the designated Foundation address. For full details, please refer to the CIP-0067.

Texture Capital Inc is a subsidiary of Texture Capital Holdings and a FINRA member broker-dealer and operator of an SEC registered Alternative Trading System.Texture Transfer Services is a separate subsidiary that is an SEC-registered transfer agent. Our unique U.S. regulatory status allows us to compliantly issue digital securities and operate secondary markets. Today, Texture Capital already offers a issuer platform where subscribers can onboard and begin raising capital immediately.

IntellectEU has completed its milestone(s) set in the CIP-0058. The voting proposal is to mint a portion of the Unclaimed Rewards by IntellectEU’s Validator, based on the calculation approved by the Tokenomics working group.
